      <processinfo id="aspace_394ebaa9331cbede60c2b73d89b13f2b">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_77d1f6c7cc39e2facd2ee04703785c19">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes, sermons, a visitors register, and bulletins documenting the activities of the Church of Christ in Yale University. Also included are the records of Charles Krigbaum, university organist and choir director.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_2319359a67e967b64f49e5fdcd480165">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
